XSLT 2.0: 5.7.1 Constructing Complex Content

A mixture of text nodes and atomic values. They all end up getting merged into
the one text node, except the atomic values are separated by spaces.

=================================== PROGRAM ====================================
gridxslt runtests.tmp/in.xml runtests.tmp/test.xsl
===================================== FILE =====================================
in.xml
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<people>
  <person>
    <name>Fred</name>
    <age>20</age>
    <occupation>Plumber</occupation>
  </person>
  <person>
    <name>Joe</name>
    <age>33</age>
    <occupation>Marketing executive</occupation>
  </person>
  <person>
    <name>Bob</name>
    <age>38</age>
    <occupation>Builder</occupation>
  </person>
</people>
===================================== FILE =====================================
test.xsl
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<xsl:transform xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" version="2.0">
  <xsl:output indent="yes"/>
  <xsl:template match="/">
    <output>
      <xsl:sequence select="/people/person/name/text(),1,2,3,/people/person/age/text()"/>
    </output>
  </xsl:template>
</xsl:transform>
==================================== OUTPUT ====================================
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<output>FredJoeBob1 2 3203338</output>
